בר עשׁ/פמ / /ITmipesha rav/XX / of grave wrongdoing is a wordplay on the boldly
contrasting /ITumipaz rav/XX, "and greater than the purest gold," eight lines ear-
lier, expressing the sharp difference between the perfection of divine utter-
ance and the human imperfection of the psalmòs speaker.    /SC/XXJ.R./XX/PR

/PR

םתיא זא / then might I be perfect--the phrase is rendered in a subjunctive
mood ("might" instead of "shall") to express the uncertainty and
wishfulness--perhaps even wistfulness--of the speaker, who knows that
even with Godòs help total human perfection is unattainable.    /SC/XXJ.R./XX/PR

